======================================================================
PART 4: π IN THE HYPERCUBE — VOLUMES AND ANGLES
======================================================================

  The hypercube Q_m in R^m has diagonal length √m.
  The inscribed sphere has radius √m/2.
  Its volume is:
    V_sphere(√m/2) = π^{m/2} / Γ(m/2 + 1) × (√m/2)^m

  For tournament hypercubes:

